      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CIRCUS MAXIMUS (3) fought on for third last start over 1200m at Blackall, making it two minor placings in a row. Has the speed to be prominent from the outset. This looks a sterner test than last time but on his best form he is right in contention. ARE YA THERE (1) debuted two weeks ago and was well supported when he finished eighth over 1200m at Blackall, beaten 16 lengths. Will be better for that run. Leading contender. ASK ME HARRY (9) finished tenth two runs back then improved last start but found one better over 800m at Thangool, beaten only 1.2 lengths after being in the firing line on the corner. Steps up a level but she is capable of running a bold race. BEL SONG (5) finished second last start at the first run back from a spell over 1200m at Blackall, beaten 2.25 lengths. Goes up a rung or two but she is good enough to make a big impact.",
